    "updated_at": "2015-01-02T23:32:30Z",
    "body": "Hi, i needed the same thing and hacked it in. i am not a C programmer by trade so my implementation is far from fancy, but it works. The downside is that the JS API doesn't recognize the default value and therefore makes my new parameter mandatory. Not ideal for a osx-only feature. Couldn't figure it out.\n\nMaybe someone from the team can look over this. -> https://github.com/m3nt0r/atom-shell/commit/214901ffeb55bcdb51a7484a327f4dd8b52dcc24\n\nSince there's hardly a reason to not support \"dark mode\" on the menubar i have enabled it by default. You could then always disable it via setImage if required:\n\n``` js\n  appIcon.setImage('img/tray.png', false); // disable the behavior\n```\n"
  },
