    "created_at": "2015-01-03T00:31:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-01-03T00:31:27Z",
    "body": "I'm more willing to support template images in the [implicit image API](https://github.com/atom/atom-shell/blob/master/atom/common/native_mate_converters/image_converter.cc) instead of in Tray API.\n\nAs quoted from [NSImage documentation](https://developer.apple.com/library/mac/documentation/Cocoa/Reference/ApplicationKit/Classes/NSImage_Class/index.html#//apple_ref/occ/clm/NSImage/imageNamed:):\n\n> If an app is linked in Mac OS X v10.5 or later, images requested using this method and whose name ends in the word “Template” are automatically marked as template images.\n\nWe can use the same behavior in atom-shell that images have `Template` suffixed in its name will be treated as template images.\n"
  },
